            . I am apprentice to my father, who lives in Bear-street, Leicester-square. On the afternoon of the 15th of December I was walking in <placeName id="t18320105-83-crimeloc469">Princes-street, Soho</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320105-83-crimeloc469" type="placeName" value="Princes-street, Soho"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320105-83-crimeloc469" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320105-83-off467 t18320105-83-crimeloc469"></join>; I stopped opposite a book shop, and saw the prisoner looking at some books - I watched, and saw him take two books from a shelf inside of the window; he walked away - I took him at the corner of King-street; I told him he had taken two books - he said he had not; I took hold of his collar, and with assistance got him to the watch-house - these two books were under his arm.</p>
